---
description: style to use when making up a commit message
globs: 
alwaysApply: false
---
- Commits should be no longer than a paragraph
- Commits should use the following syntax <type>(<scope>): <description>
| Type       | Meaning                         |
| ---------- | ------------------------------- |
| `feat`     | New feature                     |
| `fix`      | Bug fix                         |
| `chore`    | Routine task (e.g., deps)       |
| `refactor` | Code change w/o behavior change |
| `docs`     | Documentation changes           |
| `test`     | Adding or fixing tests          |
| `style`    | Formatting, linting, etc.       |
| `perf`     | Performance improvement         |
| `ci`       | CI/CD changes                   |
